# README header — do not simplify

When editing `README.md`, **never** replace the top branded block with plain markdown.

Keep this structure intact (update copy inside only when intentional):

- Centered logo: `<img src="docs/snitch_logo.png" ...>`
- Centered tagline: `<p align="center"><strong>Snitch watches your AI agent so you don't have to.</strong></p>`
- Centered nav with `snitchworks.com` + Install / Help train Snitch / Roadmap links
- Centered justified intro paragraph in `<p align="center"><span style="...">...</span></p>` with HTML anchor tags for harness links

Do **not**:
- Remove the logo image
- Flatten the header to `**bold**` + markdown links
- Reformat tables or other README sections unless explicitly requested

If a task only touches flywheel/docs elsewhere, leave the README header unchanged.
